the troublemakers.

93
00:08:41,554 --> 00:08:46,857
A couple of teenagers
acting dangerous, tough.

94
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:48,620
I had my first job here.

95
00:08:48,828 --> 00:08:52,026
- You were a lifeguard?
- No. Junior janitor.

96
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:57,865
I'd get here at 6 a.m., sweep up,
mop the locker rooms, skim the pool.

97
00:08:58,038 --> 00:09:00,098
$1.25 an hour.

98
00:09:00,273 --> 00:09:02,208
That's slave wages.

99
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:05,903
It was enough to keep me in
new records and good weed.

100
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:13,483
What? You know,
records, LPs, vinyls.

101
00:09:13,653 --> 00:09:17,613
Those funny, big, black things that your
hip-hop heroes rip off for their songs.

102
00:09:20,727 --> 00:09:22,218
Come on.

103
00:09:22,662 --> 00:09:25,131
I wanna show you something,
just a couple blocks away.

104
00:09:25,298 --> 00:09:30,100
Sixteen-inch guns could lob
a 2000-pound shell 23 miles.

105
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:34,071
When a bombardment commenced,
you could hear it 40 miles away.

106
00:09:34,474 --> 00:09:38,969
Up there's where the Japanese
surrendered. Tokyo Harbor.

107
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:42,579
Your grandfather took
me up to the bridge once.

108
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:46,948
Not here on the <i>Missouri</i>, but on
a sub tender that he was the XO of.

109
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:51,353
They used to let sailors bring families
onboard, steam around the harbor.

110
00:09:51,524 --> 00:09:56,155
Kind of a take-your-kid-to-work
day, only Dad's office was a warship.

111
00:09:56,629 --> 00:10:00,999
He introduced me to all the
sailors on watch, stuck a hat on me.

112
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:05,127
- One of those white Gilligan things?
- Yeah.

113
00:10:05,505 --> 00:10:10,671
Held me up so I could man the helm,
showed me what everything was for.

114
00:10:10,844 --> 00:10:12,335
I was about your age.

115
00:10:14,047 --> 00:10:16,016
Sounds like you liked it.

116
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:18,341
I did.

117
00:10:19,052 --> 00:10:21,180
So why didn't you join the Navy?

118
00:10:22,822 --> 00:10:24,415
I was mad at my dad.

119
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:29,524
- For what?
- Never being around, I guess.

120
00:10:30,363 --> 00:10:32,855
We used to fight all the time.

121
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:38,832
About music I listened to, my clothes,
my friends, the length of my hair.

122
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:44,041
Don't laugh, I used
to have hair. Lots of it.

123
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:46,370
Down to my shoulders.

124
00:10:48,882 --> 00:10:52,978
He resented my
politics. I hated his.

125
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:57,090
