putting in your body when you're 16?

251
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:14,096
We're gonna talk about this.

252
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,902
Rachel, damn it, stop.

253
00:21:18,043 --> 00:21:21,445
I love you. Please,
don't do this.

254
00:21:21,614 --> 00:21:23,173
I don't...

255
00:21:24,183 --> 00:21:26,118
I don't know what to do.

256
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:30,746
I don't have time to work this through.
I'm not gonna be here in a year to help.

257
00:21:30,923 --> 00:21:34,052
You got a bastard of a
father who was never around...

258
00:21:34,226 --> 00:21:36,388
and then went off
and had a new baby.

259
00:21:36,562 --> 00:21:39,691
Your mom got remarried to
a creep, she works too much.

260
00:21:39,865 --> 00:21:44,428
You got a raw deal, all
right? Why not get high?

261
00:21:44,637 --> 00:21:46,765
No one gives a damn
about you anyway.

262
00:21:46,939 --> 00:21:49,408
I know how that feels.

263
00:21:49,909 --> 00:21:55,075
I remember being 14 and
pissed off at my dad and the world.

264
00:21:56,215 --> 00:21:58,150
What are you gonna
do when I'm not here?

265
00:21:58,317 --> 00:22:02,254
Who is gonna keep you from
killing yourself? I'm scared.

266
00:22:02,588 --> 00:22:05,285
Scared about what's
gonna happen to you.

267
00:22:05,891 --> 00:22:10,090
Look, it sucks! I'm your
father, and I'm gonna die.

268
00:22:10,262 --> 00:22:13,721
You know what?
I think it sucks too.

269
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,503
No, it's... Yeah.

270
00:22:24,677 --> 00:22:26,339
No, it's fine.

271
00:22:26,612 --> 00:22:28,342
I'm great.

272
00:22:29,448 --> 00:22:30,780
No, I'm feeling good.

273
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:32,441
<i>- All right.</i>
- How's Ella?

274
00:22:32,618 --> 00:22:35,452
<i>She's wonderful. The
tooth finally grew in.</i>

275
00:22:35,621 --> 00:22:36,850
- Really?
<i>- Yeah, finally.</i>

276
00:22:37,056 --> 00:22:39,355
- That's great.
<i>- How's Rachel doing?</i>

277
00:22:39,859 --> 00:22:41,828
She's fine.

278
00:22:42,494 --> 00:22:44,258
You know...

279
00:22:44,496 --> 00:22:45,987
fourteen.

280
00:23:13,893 --> 00:23:15,862
You wanna go out
to dinner or eat here?

281
00:23:16,028 --> 00:23:18,497
I think we have
some of that ono left.

282
00:23:18,664 --> 00:23:20,826
Vegetables, ice...

283
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,162
I want pizza. Can
we get some pizza?

284
00:23:23,335 --> 00:23:26,828
There's that place down by the surf
shop that looked pretty good. Some olive...

285
00:23:28,741 --> 00:23:30,232
Dad?

286
00:23:30,609 --> 00:23:32,373
God, Dad?

287
00:23:33,112 --> 00:23:35,911
Dad? Dad?

288
00:24:09,782 --> 00:24:11,273
Mark?

289
00:24:15,654 --> 00:24:17,145
Mark!

290
00:24:20,459 --> 00:24:22,587
Oh, my goodness, look.

291
00:24:28,634 --> 00:24:30,125
Mark?

292
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:41,644
Hi.

293
00:24:47,386 --> 00:24:48,945
Hi.

294
00:24:53,225 --> 00:24:56,457
We were out driving around,
I saw the vacation-rental sign.

295
00:24:56,628 --> 00:25:00,656
- It must cost a fortune.
- You only live once.

296
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:05,003
There's a lady named Janet. She
lives up the road, takes care of children.

297
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:07,162
She said she'd be
happy to help out.

298
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:11,970
- Huh. What's this?
- Herbs. Got a whole bunch of them.

299
00:25:12,144 --> 00:25:16,081
Take them in the morning, the
afternoon. Boosts my immune system.

300
00:25:16,248 --> 00:25:18,911
- Is this snakeskin?
- Could be.

301
00:25:19,118 --> 00:25:22,486
The lady who does my
acupuncture gave them to me.

302
00:25:22,654 --> 00:25:24,179
Couldn't hurt.

303
00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:26,723
I can't find a corkscrew.
How about a beer?

304
00:25:26,892 --> 00:25:28,383
Sure.

305
00:25:29,328 --> 00:25:31,229
So where's Rachel?

306
00:25:31,430 --> 00:25:33,262
She's out surfing.

307
00:25:36,201 --> 00:25:38,534
She found you in a
grand mal seizure.

308
00:25:39,171 --> 00:25:40,434
It's no big deal.

309
00:25:40,639 --> 00:25:42,870
She was scared to
death when she called me.

310
00:25:43,042 --> 00:25:46,206
- What did the neurologist say?
- Up the Dilantin to 400.

311
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:48,370
You didn't see a doctor?

312
00:25:48,714 --> 00:25:50,945
- Nope.
- How do you know what your level is?

313
00:25:51,583 --> 00:25:52,949
I'm fine.

314
00:25:53,152 --> 00:25:55,212
Mark, you need a CAT
scan and a full workup.

315
00:25:55,954 --> 00:25:57,684
No, thanks.

316
00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:03,525
Take my hand. Come on.

317
00:26:03,695 --> 00:26:05,561
Squeeze my fingers.

318
00:26:11,670 --> 00:26:13,662
What about your wrist?

319
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,936
Your elbow?

320
00:26:19,278 --> 00:26:20,803
All right, we're going home.

321
00:26:20,979 --> 00:26:24,108
You need an MRI and
to see the neurologist.

322
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:26,241
No.

323
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:31,053
I don't wanna go back home.

324
00:26:37,396 --> 00:26:40,093
It's beautiful here, isn't it?

325
00:26:43,335 --> 00:26:45,634
Come on, let me
show you the beach.

326
00:26:50,776 --> 00:26:53,177
What's she gonna do with
a surfboard in St. Louis?

327
00:26:53,345 --> 00:26:55,314
Let it gather dust
in the garage.

328
00:26:55,481 --> 00:26:58,610
- Has she been like this the whole time?
- Pretty much.

329
00:26:58,784 --> 00:27:00,275
Lucky you.

330
00:27:00,452 --> 00:27:04,150
- Hey, I never knew they were so tall.
- Some are. Some aren't.

331
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:13,964
Hey, I'm looking for a long
board for my daughter. She's 14.

332
00:27:14,133 --> 00:27:18,503
- How long were you thinking?
- Nine, 9'1". Maybe a Hamilton.

333
00:27:20,506 --> 00:27:22,771
- What's she doing?
- It's okay.

334
00:27:22,941 --> 00:27:25,877
- Does she even want a surfboard?
- Watch this.

335
00:27:26,044 --> 00:27:27,535
I know.

336
00:27:27,746 --> 00:27:30,306
- Who's he?
- Don't stare. It'll upset her.

337
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:33,145
- Well, does she know him?
- He works here. His name's Kai.

338
00:27:33,318 --> 00:27:36,550
- Kai?
- Kai. It means "ocean."

339
00:27:36,755 --> 00:27:41,125
She's made up a new excuse why we
had to come back the last three days.

340
00:27:42,161 --> 00:27:43,652
- How old is he?
- I don't know.

341
00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:45,821
- He looks at least 16.
- Could be.

342
00:27:45,998 --> 00:27:47,489
Maybe 17.

343
00:27:47,666 --> 00:27:50,727
I have some boards she might
like. A Papa San and a Sunburnt.

344
00:27:50,903 --> 00:27:52,394
Good.

345
00:28:34,746 --> 00:28:37,511
Rachel, can you
come and help me?

346
00:28:48,694 --> 00:28:51,459
Remember when I
used to sing you to sleep?

347
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,221
No.

348
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:57,570
You made me do it for years.

349
00:29:00,072 --> 00:29:03,565
You watched <i>The Wizard of
Oz</i> and <i>The Little Mermaid...</i>

350
00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:09,079
over and over again.
It'd drive me crazy.

351
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:15,585
We had that apartment off of Division
with the big iron gates out front...

352
00:29:15,754 --> 00:29:18,656
and that funny-looking
mutt next door. Dudley?

353
00:29:18,857 --> 00:29:20,257
Dad.

354
00:29:20,425 --> 00:29:23,486
There was a playground across
the street. Remember the big slide?

355
00:29:23,662 --> 00:29:25,153
I don't.

356
00:29:25,364 --> 00:29:28,095
I don't remember, okay? I
don't remember any of that stuff!

357
00:29:28,267 --> 00:29:32,432
It's not important! And you just
keep talking and talking about it!

358
00:29:32,604 --> 00:29:34,505
- It is important.
- No, it's not!

359
00:29:35,173 --> 00:29:37,642
Where you used to live,
where we used to live...

360
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:41,746
and Grandmom's stupid garden,
Granddad's cousin Dave, or whatever.

361
00:29:41,913 --> 00:29:44,940
Rachel, keep your voice
down. The baby's sleeping.

362
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:51,249
I'm trying to tell you about
us, about our family, our history.

363
00:29:51,423 --> 00:29:54,951
- It's stupid, boring, useless crap!
- It's not crap!

364
00:29:55,127 --> 00:29:57,289
- Some dog named Dudley?
- You loved that dog.

365
00:29:57,462 --> 00:30:00,523
I don't care about these things!
I don't wanna hear this stuff!

366
00:30:00,699 --> 00:30:03,965
So just stop talking
to me about it.

367
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,039
I'll go.

368
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:43,502
How long are you
planning on keeping this up?

369
00:30:46,545 --> 00:30:49,845
He's not perfect. Far from it.

370
00:30:50,315 --> 00:30:52,546
But he's trying.

371
00:30:54,353 --> 00:30:57,016
You've got to grow up faster
than you should have to.

372
00:30:57,189 --> 00:31:00,353
You don't get to be a child
anymore. Your father's dying.

373
00:31:00,525 --> 00:31:02,357
I know that.

374
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:07,697
He's going to die
soon. Very soon.

375
00:31:07,966 --> 00:31:12,870
If you keep on like this, you're gonna miss
what little time you have left with him.

376
00:31:16,241 --> 00:31:18,904
This is it, Rachel.

377
00:31:19,077 --> 00:31:21,546
This is your last chance.

378
00:31:22,481 --> 00:31:28,182
And if you blow it, you're gonna end up
hating yourself for the rest of your life.

379
00:32:46,498 --> 00:32:47,989
Shit!

380
00:33:10,856 --> 00:33:12,950
I'm a bit worried
about that cough.

381
00:33:13,124 --> 00:33:14,319
It's okay.

382
00:33:14,493 --> 00:33:17,327
We could go to the hospital,
get a CBC and a chest x-ray.

383
00:33:17,496 --> 00:33:18,794
No, thanks.

384
00:33:18,964 --> 00:33:21,729
Mark, the Decadron's
suppressing your immune system.

385
00:33:21,933 --> 00:33:23,196
No kidding.

386
00:33:23,368 --> 00:33:25,428
Did you up it again?

387
00:33:25,804 --> 00:33:29,241
Okay, well, if it turns to pneumonia,
we can give IV antibiotics.

388
00:33:29,441 --> 00:33:30,670
- Pneumonia, huh?
- Uh-huh.

389
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:33,311
That's not a bad way to go.

390
00:33:36,581 --> 00:33:38,072
Okay.

391
00:33:38,717 --> 00:33:40,481
There you go.

392
00:33:41,152 --> 00:33:44,884
- Where's Rachel?
- She's at Sunset with Kai.

393
00:33:45,056 --> 00:33:46,524
Mm.

394
00:33:46,691 --> 00:33:49,183
Nice offshore breeze.

395
00:33:49,561 --> 00:33:51,655
Waves should be great.

396
00:33:53,598 --> 00:33:55,760
They're spending a
great deal of time together.

397
00:33:57,168 --> 00:33:59,160
He's a nice kid.

398
00:34:00,572 --> 00:34:01,835
So you're not worried?

399
00:34:02,908 --> 00:34:04,604
About what?

400
00:34:04,776 --> 00:34:06,938
About what they might
be doing in all that time.

401
00:34:07,112 --> 00:34:08,603
No.

402
00:34:09,581 --> 00:34:11,709
I think it's great.

403
00:34:17,722 --> 00:34:19,520
I need you to do
something for me.

404
00:34:20,625 --> 00:34:23,288
- Mm-hm.
- It might be kind of hard.

405
00:34:25,764 --> 00:34:30,031
I wanna write letters
to Rachel and Ella.

406
00:34:30,702 --> 00:34:33,297
I tried to do it myself...

407
00:34:33,505 --> 00:34:35,701
but I can't read my
own writing now.

408
00:34:42,781 --> 00:34:46,445
I want them to open
letters on special days.

409
00:34:47,652 --> 00:34:49,245
You know?

410
00:34:49,454 --> 00:34:53,084
High-school
graduation, college...

411
00:34:53,525 --> 00:34:54,891
their wedding days.

412
00:35:01,399 --> 00:35:03,527
Think that's cruel?

413
00:35:04,736 --> 00:35:08,673
Reaching out from beyond the grave
on days when they should be happy?

414
00:35:12,143 --> 00:35:15,113
I think they'll cherish
every single word.

415
00:35:22,921 --> 00:35:24,753
Told you it might be hard.

416
00:35:27,425 --> 00:35:29,360
I'm okay.

417
00:35:53,385 --> 00:35:55,286
Is he asleep?

418
00:35:55,453 --> 00:35:56,944
Yep.

419
00:35:59,691 --> 00:36:00,954
He sleeps a lot now.

420
00:36:02,293 --> 00:36:03,784
Yeah.

421
00:36:12,604 --> 00:36:14,300
He's in a lot of pain.

422
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:17,302
It won't be long now.

423
00:37:00,051 --> 00:37:01,576
Hi.

424
00:37:02,654 --> 00:37:04,020
Hi.

425
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:07,916
I was just dreaming about you.

426
00:37:08,693 --> 00:37:12,152
- You were?
- When you used to love balloons.

427
00:37:14,099 --> 00:37:16,261
You remember how
much you loved balloons?

428
00:37:17,435 --> 00:37:21,202
- No.
- I used to buy them for you.

429
00:37:22,073 --> 00:37:25,441
And right when I
handed them to you...

430
00:37:26,411 --> 00:37:28,539
you'd let them go.

431
00:37:28,713 --> 00:37:31,581
Drive your mother crazy.

432
00:37:33,418 --> 00:37:36,286
Sit with me. Sit down.

433
00:37:37,222 --> 00:37:38,713
Sit.

434
00:37:42,761 --> 00:37:45,731
I was trying to figure out...

435
00:37:46,231 --> 00:37:51,135
what I should have already
told you but I never have.

436
00:37:51,803 --> 00:37:53,135
Something important.

437
00:37:53,304 --> 00:37:58,902
Something every father
should impart to his daughter.

438
00:38:01,446 --> 00:38:03,312
I finally got it.

439
00:38:05,817 --> 00:38:07,479
Generosity.

440
00:38:09,721 --> 00:38:12,850
Be generous...

441
00:38:13,658 --> 00:38:16,787
with your time...

442
00:38:18,096 --> 00:38:20,861
with your love...

443
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:24,736
with your life.

444
00:38:26,271 --> 00:38:27,762
Okay.

445
00:38:29,507 --> 00:38:32,033
I'm sorry, Rachel.

446
00:38:32,877 --> 00:38:36,678
- I'm so tired.
- It's okay.

447
00:38:37,182 --> 00:38:40,516
Don't cry for me.

448
00:38:44,289 --> 00:38:45,780
I won't.

449
00:38:46,758 --> 00:38:48,784
Be generous...

450
00:38:52,397 --> 00:38:53,888
always.

451
00:38:56,634 --> 00:38:58,125
I will.

452
00:39:03,308 --> 00:39:04,799
Daddy?

453
00:39:10,648 --> 00:39:12,879
I remember the lullaby.

454
00:39:14,652 --> 00:39:17,349
I remember you used to
sing it to me every night.

455
00:39:30,869 --> 00:39:32,599
I remember.

456
00:39:58,263 --> 00:40:00,255
It's a sheep. Baa!

457
00:42:13,197 --> 00:42:16,361
The resurrection and
the life, saith the Lord...

458
00:42:18,569 --> 00:42:21,869
though he were
dead, yet shall he live.

459
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:25,477
And whosoever liveth and
believeth in me shall never die.

460
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:28,676
I know that my
redeemer liveth...

461
00:42:28,846 --> 00:42:31,372
and he shall stand at the
latter day upon the Earth.

462
00:42:32,550 --> 00:42:35,247
And though his
body be destroyed...

463
00:43:28,673 --> 00:43:30,266
Can I still come see Ella?

464
00:43:31,776 --> 00:43:35,144
Summers or at Christmas?

465
00:43:35,580 --> 00:43:38,277
Of course. She's your sister.

466
00:43:45,756 --> 00:43:48,624
Hey! Hey, hey, can
you pull over, please?

467
00:43:48,793 --> 00:43:50,193
- What?
- Right here.
